// pipeMaterial      — what most homes actually have
// infraClass        — 'aging' | 'mixed' | 'modern'
// winterRisk        — 'high' | 'med' | 'low'
// avgWinterTempF    — integer degrees Fahrenheit
// summerRiskNote    — summer-specific issue (unique per city)
// dominantFailure   — the #1 plumbing problem in this city
// sewerSystem       — sewer infrastructure note
// soilType          — soil/geology that affects pipes
// zipCodes          — real representative zip codes
// pop               — population string
// climate           — climate classification
// infraNarrative    — 2-sentence unique infra paragraph
// ============================================================
